gomodel:SYNGO_5113  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: \"To assess the mechanism underlying its synaptic targeting, we performed immunocytochemical assays on GFP-SPIN90-transfected hippocampal neurons. Anti-SPIN90 antibody clearly stained GFP-SPIN90 spots, as revealed by an exact match between GFP signals and signals generated by immunostaining with anti-SPIN90 antibody (Fig. 1A). Moreover GFP-SPIN90 accumulated at spines in association with the postsynaptic marker, PSD95, and adjacent to the presynaptic marker, Vamp2 (Fig. 1B)\"\n\nFigure 4, 5: SPIN90 (NCKIPSD) phosphorylation increased its postsynaptic localization and binds PSD95 (DLG4) and Shank with increased efficiency.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 1 legend: \"Rat hippocampal neurons transfected with GFP-SPIN90 at DIV 10-12 were fixed at DIV 19-21 and labeled with the indicated antibodies\"\n\nantibody:\nPolyclonal anti-SPIN90 serum was described previously PMID:21763308" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5113" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

